cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use BidReader in your work, please cite it."
title: "BidReader: structured extraction and scope-gap detection from construction bid documents"
abstract: >-
  An MIT-licensed Python library, CLI, and MCP server that reads construction
  sub-quotes, bid packages, and spec PDFs into clean, page-cited structured data
  and flags scope gaps and exclusions buried in vendor fine print.
type: software
authors:
